# Architecture

The {{ project_name | title }} extension follows the standard OWI Metadatabase SDK
extension pattern: inherit from the base `API` class and append a
sub-path to `api_root`.

## Layer Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph Client Code
        U[User script / notebook]
    end

    subgraph Extension SDK
        API[{{ project_name | replace('-', ' ') | title | replace(' ', '') }}API]
    end

    subgraph Base SDK
        BASE[owi.metadatabase.io.API]
    end

    subgraph Backend
        REST[Django REST API]
    end

    U --> API
    API -->|inherits| BASE
    BASE -->|HTTP| REST
```

## Request Lifecycle

1. User calls a method on the extension API.
2. The method builds URL parameters and delegates to `self.process_data()`.
3. The base SDK performs a health check, sends the HTTP request, and
   decodes JSON into a DataFrame.
4. The extension post-processes and returns the typed result.

## Extension Point

New extension packages created from this template should:

- Add domain-specific methods to the API class.
- Return `{"data": DataFrame, "exists": bool}` from list endpoints.
- Keep the `api_subdir` default pointing to the correct backend path.
